# 42 : CONTENT_SUBSCRIPTION — follow-creator + auto-pull-new-content
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# § T11-W12-SUBSCRIBE — sibling-of W12-4 ContentPackage + W12-5 Publish
#                     · LEVERAGES W11-11 cssl-hotfix channel-mechanism
#                     · LEVERAGES W11-8 cssl-mycelium-chat-sync federation

§ THESIS
  consent = OS  ←  ∀ subscribe ⊑ explicit-pull · ¬ implicit-bind
  sovereign-unsubscribe ⊑ always-available · halt-cascade · purge-feed
  ¬ engagement-bait ; ¬ auto-resurface ; ¬ surveillance-of-feed
  cascade-revoke ⊑ creator-revoke ∨ moderation-revoke ⇒ subscriber-notif
                   ⊕ CONSENT-GATED removal-from-installed (¬ silent-delete)
  k-anon ≥ 10 ⊑ aggregate-counts (trending) gate ; ¬ exposure < 10

§ TARGET-KINDS  (3)
  Creator      = ⟨pubkey-32B⟩       Q? follow-author across-all-content
  Tag          = ⟨tag-string-1..64⟩ Q? follow-topical-cluster
  ContentChain = ⟨root-id-32B⟩      Q? follow-remix-chain (sibling-W12-9)

§ FREQUENCY  (3)
  Realtime  ⊑ push-on-event · rate-limit ≤ 1 / 60 s default
  Daily     ⊑ digest-rollup · 1 / 24 h
  Manual    ⊑ pull-only · ¬ auto-push (player initiates)

§ NOTIFICATION-KINDS  (5)
  NewPublished        I> creator/tag/chain has-new-content
  RemixCreated        I> someone-remixed your-followed-content
  UpdateAvailable     I> new-version of subscribed-content
  RevokedByCreator    I> creator-revoke cascade · CONSENT-GATED removal
  RevokedByModeration I> mod-revoke cascade · reason-tag · APPEALABLE
  ∀ kind ⊑ auto_resurfaceable() = false  ←  ENCODED STRUCTURALLY

§ ANTI-SPAM
  rate-limit-default = 1 notif / 60 s / subscriber  (token-bucket)
  daily-digest = 1 notif / 24 h / subscriber  (digest-rollup pure-fn)
  ¬ auto-resurface ←  read_at_ns set ⇒ ¬ re-surface
  cap-X-creator-revoke ⊕ cap-X-moderation-revoke ⊑ rate-limit-bypass
                                                   ∵ safety-critical

§ CASCADING-REVOKE  (numbered flow)
  1) sibling-W12-5 OR sibling-W12-11 emits RevokeEvent
       { content_id · revoker_pubkey · reason · audience_sigma_mask · ts_ns }
  2) /api/content/cascade-publish receives event (cap-gated)
  3) lookup ACTIVE subs matching ⟨target_kind=creator, target_id=revoker⟩
                          ∪ ⟨target_kind=content-chain, target_id=content_id⟩
  4) ∀ matching-sub : Σ-mask AND-overlap-check ; INSERT notif of kind
       RevokedBy⟨Creator|Moderation⟩ with reason ≤ 200 chars
  5) subscriber app receives push-notification (rate-limit-bypassed)
  6) subscriber sees CONSENT-DIALOG : keep-installed ∨ remove-installed
       (host crate W12-N6 wires the dialog ; ¬ in this slice)

§ Σ-MASK GATE
  per-subscription mask-byte ⊆ audience-mask-byte  ⇒  notif-emitted
  per-subscription mask-byte ∩ audience-mask-byte = ∅  ⇒  notif-DROPPED
  16-byte audience-class · creator-class ¬ leak ⇒ moderator-class

§ HOTFIX-CHANNEL LEVERAGE  (¬ duplicate)
  reuse SUBSCRIBE_CHANNEL_NAME = "content.subscribed.realtime"
  ⊑ existing 9-channel cssl-hotfix manifest path
  ⊑ host-bridge crate W12-N6 wires hotfix-client → SubscribeAdapter

§ K-ANON AGGREGATE  (trending without exposure)
  content_subscription_aggregates table ⊑ k-anon ≥ 10 enforced via
    HAVING COUNT(*) ≥ 10 in rebuild_content_subscription_aggregates()
  rebuild = scheduled-job (¬ in this slice ; sibling-cron pattern)
  W12-6 discover-pages reads aggregates · displays trending
  ¬ exposure-of-individuals · ¬ leak-via-low-count

§ ENDPOINTS  (4 · cssl-edge)
  POST /api/content/subscribe       I> create row · cap-gated · self-pubkey
  POST /api/content/unsubscribe     I> revoke + purge feed-rows
   GET /api/content/notifications   I> read unread feed (own only)
  POST /api/content/notifications   I> mark-read action (ids: [...])
  POST /api/content/cascade-publish I> internal · sibling-emitted ·
                                       cap CONTENT_CAP_PUBLISH ∨ REVOKE_ANY

§ SQL-SCHEMA  (0029_content_subscriptions.sql)
  content_subscriptions             pk-text ⊕ FK from notifications
  content_notifications             pk-text ⊕ FK ON DELETE CASCADE
  content_subscription_aggregates   pk-(target_kind,target_id) ⊕ k-anon ≥ 10
  ALL ⊑ RLS-enabled · self-read ∨ service-role · service-write-only

§ ATTESTATION  ( PRIME_DIRECTIVE.md § 11 — encoded structurally )
  ¬ harm  ¬ control  ¬ surveillance  ¬ exploitation  ¬ engagement-bait
  ✓ sovereign-unsubscribe always-1-call ✓ cascade-revoke-consent-gated
  ✓ Σ-mask-gated ✓ rate-limit-default-1-per-min ✓ k-anon-aggregate-≥-10
  ✓ no-auto-resurface ENCODED STRUCTURALLY
